# Phase 0 — Why This Exists

## Historical Context

Traditional recruitment relies heavily on:

* Job Boards
* Keyword Search
* Manual Screening
* Recruiter Experience

Typical workflow:

```text
Job Opening
      ↓
Recruiter Search
      ↓
Resume Review
      ↓
Interview Selection
```

Problems emerge when:

* Thousands of applications arrive
* Candidates use different terminology
* Recruiters miss qualified talent
* Screening becomes expensive

AI enables:

```text
Job Description
      ↓
AI Understanding
      ↓
Candidate Search
      ↓
Ranking
      ↓
Recruiter Review
```

---

## Problems It Solves

### Problem 1

Keyword search misses qualified candidates.

Example:

```text
Job Requires:
Python

Candidate Uses:
Backend Engineering
Automation Development
```

Keyword matching fails.

---

### Problem 2

Recruiters spend hours reviewing resumes.

---

### Problem 3

Candidate ranking is inconsistent.

---

### Problem 4

Large candidate databases become difficult to search.

---

### Problem 5

Skills evolve faster than manual taxonomies.

---

